肉食主義的核心觀點就是把動物分成可食用、不可食用、寵物、[[Vermin|有害動物]]、掠食者、娛樂動物，而這些分類是根據人們的[[Schema_(psychology)|基模]]而定的，這種心理分類可左右我們的信念與欲望，反之亦然<ref name="Gibert2014" /><ref name="Joy2011pp14,17" />。至於哪些動物算是食物，則依文化而異。狗在中國與南韓是可食用的，但其他地方的人卻不把狗視為食物，可能是因為人類喜愛狗，也可能是因為人認為狗是不潔的，中東與印度部分地區就是如此<ref name="Gibert2014" /><!-- <ref name="Podberscek2009" /> --><ref>Herzog, Hal (2011). [https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/animals-and-us/201106/having-your-dog-and-eating-it-too "Having Your Dog and Eating It Too?"], ''Psychology Today''.</ref>。牛在西方是食物，但在印度卻是備受崇敬。豬遭受穆斯林與猶太人的排斥，其他團體卻廣泛認為豬肉可食用<ref name="Winzeler2012">{{cite book|author=Robert L. Winzeler|title=Anthropology and Religion: What We Know, Think, and Question|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mREqLR4uqp8C&pg=PA63|date=12 April 2012|publisher=AltaMira Press|isbn=978-0-7591-2191-1|pages=63}}</ref><!--  LAVIN SOURCE UNDEFINED: <ref>Lavin 2013, pp. 116–117.</ref>-->。喬伊和其他心理學者認為，這些分類法左右了動物受到的對待，影響了人類對動物的知覺與智力所抱持之主觀認知，而人對動物的[[同理心|同理心]]與道德關注也會隨之增減<ref name=Joy2011pp14,17>Joy 2011, pp. 14, 17.</ref>。

=== 肉品悖論 ===
主要文章：[[肉食心理學|肉食心理學]]與[[肉品悖論|肉品悖論]]

傑夫·曼尼斯（Jeff Mannes）寫道，多數人的價值觀與行動相互矛盾，反對傷害動物卻又吃動物，而肉食主義就是深植於這樣的矛盾之中。曼尼斯認為，這種衝突會導致[[認知失調|認知失調]]，人們嘗試以[[Psychic_numbing|精神麻痺]]的方式來稀釋衝突的強度<ref name="Mannes2015">{{cite book | url=http://www.transcript-verlag.de/978-3-8376-2232-4/lexikon-der-mensch-tier-beziehungen | title=Lexikon der Mensch-Tier-Beziehungen | chapter = Karnismus | publisher=Transcript Verlag | author=Mannes,Jeff| year=2015 | pages=191–193 | isbn=978-3-8376-2232-4}}</ref>。「關心動物」以及「接受肉食就表示必須傷害動物」，這兩種觀念間的衝突明顯易見，「[[Psychology_of_eating_meat#Meat_paradox|肉品悖論]]」一詞正是由此而來<ref name=Loughnan2014>Loughnan, Steve; Bastian, Brock; Haslam, Nick (2014). [https://foodethics.univie.ac.at/fileadmin/user_upload/inst_ethik_wiss_dialog/Loughnan__S._2014_And_Bastian._..The_Psychology_of_Eating_Animals._In._CURRENT_DIRECTIONS_IN_PSYCHOLOGICAL_SCIENCE.pdf "The Psychology of Eating Animals"] {{Wayback|url=https://foodethics.univie.ac.at/fileadmin/user_upload/inst_ethik_wiss_dialog/Loughnan__S._2014_And_Bastian._..The_Psychology_of_Eating_Animals._In._CURRENT_DIRECTIONS_IN_PSYCHOLOGICAL_SCIENCE.pdf |date=20180930183806 }}, ''Current Directions in Psychological Science'',  23(2), April, pp. 104–108. {{doi|10.1177/0963721414525781}}</ref><ref name="Loughnan2010">{{cite journal | title=The role of meat consumption in the denial of moral status and mind to meat animals | author=Loughnan, Steve| journal=Appetite |year=2010  | volume=55 | issue=1 | pages=156–159 | doi=10.1016/j.appet.2010.05.043 | pmid=20488214|display-authors=etal}}</ref><ref name=Fawcett2013p215>Fawcett, Anne (2013). "Euthanasia and morally justifiable killing in a veterinary clinical context", in Jay Johnston, Fiona Probyn-Rapsey (eds.), ''Animal Death'', Sydney: Sydney University Press, p. [https://books.google.com/books?id=BaGUOm2SRngC&pg=PA215 215].</ref>。

有實驗證明肉品悖論的確會引致西方人認知失調<ref name="Piazza2015" /><ref name="Rothgerber2014">{{cite journal | title=Efforts to overcome vegetarian-induced dissonance among meat eaters | author=Rothgerber, Hank | journal=Appetite |date=August 2014  | volume=79 | pages=32–41 | doi=10.1016/j.appet.2014.04.003}}</ref><ref>Hodson, Gordon (3 March 2014). [https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/without-prejudice/201403/the-meat-paradox-loving-exploiting-animals "The Meat Paradox: Loving but Exploiting Animals"], ''Psychology Today''.</ref>。對於在心理素質與道德地位上皆被視為次等的動物，西方人比較願意吃下肚，也會認為被吃的動物在心智能力與道德地位上較為低下<ref name="Loughnan2014" /><ref name="Bastian2011">{{cite journal | url=https://www2.psy.uq.edu.au/~uqbbast1/Bastian%20et%20al%20PSPB%20in%20press.pdf | doi=10.1177/0146167211424291 | title=Don’t mind meat? The denial of mind to animals used for human consumption | author=Bastian, Brock | journal=Personality and Social Psychology Bulletin | date=2011 | volume=38 | issue=2 | pages=247–256 | display-authors=etal | access-date=2016-10-13 | archive-date=2019-06-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190619175728/https://www2.psy.uq.edu.au/~uqbbast1/Bastian%20et%20al%20PSPB%20in%20press.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>。此外，兩者的關係也有一定的作用：動物分成食用與非食用，正好反映出人們對動物的心理特性所抱持之認知，吃肉行為本身會讓人貶低動物具備的心理能力<ref name="Loughnan2014" />。舉例來說，根據某項研究，在受試者面前提及某種不熟悉的異國動物，說當地人民會獵捕牠，那麼受試者就會覺得牠不太聰明；而在另一項研究，受試者吃了牛肉乾之後，就會覺得牛不太聰明<ref name="Loughnan2014" />。

另一項策略就是不去思考[[Animal_product|動物產品]]的出處<ref name=Plous2002>{{cite book|last1=Plous|first1=Scott|editor1-last=Plous|editor1-first=Scott|title=Understanding Prejudice and Discrimination|date=2002|publisher=McGraw Hill Higher Education|isbn=0-07-255443-6|pages=509–528|url=http://www.understandingprejudice.org/pdf/animals.pdf?logged=true|accessdate=9 August 2015|chapter=Is there such a thing as discrimination towards animals?}}</ref>。喬伊認為，這就是為什麼肉上桌時很少會連同動物的頭部或其他身體部位一起上桌<ref>Joy 2011, p. 16.</ref>。

